label: University of Pennsylvania Ms. Oversize 33: Choir psalter gatherings
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: A section (5 gatherings) from the middle of a choir psalter containing a number of psalms (part of 67 and all of 71, 74-75, 80, 83-86, 88, 90-91, 94-98, and 102-103) in order for liturgical use, followed by the first half of the hymn Te Deum with square notation in black on 5-line staves in red. Some water damage at the top of most leaves and some repairs, with replaced text in another hand, at the bottom of leaves.
        Language: Latin
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: Parchment, 40; 1¹ 2-4⁸ 5⁸(-8); modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.
        Layout: Psalms written in 15 long lines; Te Deum written in 5 lines with musical notation; psalm texts originally ruled in lead, ornamental double bounding lines and ruling in red ink added after the text was written.
        Script: Written in a rounded Gothic script.
        Decoration: 
        Binding: Gatherings stitched to 6 bands but without binding; some of the penwork was trimmed for binding.
        Origin: Written in Spain in the 16th century.
        Cite as:	
        UPenn Ms. Oversize 33
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 4270055 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/4270055
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/PennManuscripts/html/msoversize33.html
